-- Al Habtoor Buys Le Meridien Luxury Hotel in Budapest, MTI Says
-- B y   Z o l t a n   S i m o n
-- 2012-05-07T12:05:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-07/al-habtoor-buys-le-meridien-luxury-hotel-in-budapest-mti-says.html
Al Habtoor Group LLC, a Dubai-based
company owned by Khalaf Al Habtoor, bought Le Meridien hotel in
Budapest, state-run news service MTI reported.  Al Habtoor declined to specify the price paid for the five-
star hotel, which has 218 rooms and seven conference rooms and
is operated by  Starwood Hotels and Resorts Worldwide Inc. , MTI
said. The hotel was previously owned by Central European Estates
BV, the news service said. 